---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout page="colophon" title="Colophon — Priyank Sharma">
  <section class="colophon">
    <a href="/" class="colophon-back">&larr; Home</a>

    <h1 class="colophon-title">Colophon</h1>

    <div class="colophon-body">
      <p>This site is a working artifact. It changes when my thinking changes.</p>

      <p>
        Built with Astro &mdash; a content-first framework that keeps the writing
        fast and the JavaScript minimal. Hosted on Cloudflare Pages, deployed
        automatically when I push to GitHub. The reactions backend runs on
        Cloudflare Workers KV &mdash; about 80 lines of code I wrote on a Sunday
        before I knew what a terminal was.
      </p>

      <p>
        The agent on the homepage is powered by the Anthropic API &mdash; Claude
        Sonnet, with a system prompt I wrote that tries to make it sound like me.
        It mostly does.
      </p>

      <p>
        Set in Lora (serif) and Inter (sans-serif), both via Google Fonts.
        Terracotta accent at #C96F4A, chosen because every other design portfolio
        uses blue.
      </p>

      <p>
        Source on <a href="https://github.com/prishnow/PriyankSharma" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
        Feel free to look around.
      </p>
    </div>

    <hr class="colophon-hairline" />
    <p class="colophon-meta">Last updated: April 2026</p>
  </section>
</Layout>
